{"id":23841,"date":"2016-10-05T08:31:32","date_gmt":"2016-10-05T04:31:32","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=23841"},"modified":"2019-07-14T16:43:21","modified_gmt":"2019-07-14T12:43:21","slug":"conceal-hudud-if-possible","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/10\/05\/conceal-hudud-if-possible\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Pardon: Conceal legal offenses from punishment if possible"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Keep away from these ugly deeds that Allah has prohibited. Whoever falls into them should cover himself with the covering of Allah Almighty<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Al-Shafi\u2019i, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cIt is narrated from Abu Bakr, may Allah be pleased with him, that in the lifetime of the Prophet (s\u0323) he commanded a man who committed a legal offense to conceal his deed. Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, commanded the same.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Sunan al-Kubra\u0304 16177<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Hasan<\/em> (fair) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e<strong> \u0627\u062c\u0652\u062a\u064e\u0646\u0650\u0628\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0647\u064e\u0630\u0650\u0647\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0630\u064f\u0648\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0651\u064e\u062a\u0650\u064a \u0646\u064e\u0647\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0641\u06